The acclaimed musical, The Rocky Horror Picture Show, is opening on Sunday at Montecasino’s Teatro in Johannesburg and runs until 1 March. JOHANNESBURG - It's camp, funny, and a romp of a song-and-dance. The acclaimed musical, The Rocky Horror Picture Show, is opening on Sunday at Montecasino’s Teatro in Johannesburg and runs until 1 March. It’s a science fiction comedy-horror that has enticed audiences since 1973. The plot revolves around a couple, Brad and Janet, whose car breaks down one stormy night. They knock on the door of Dr Frank’n’Furter and his family of mad characters. And that’s when the song-and-dance craziness begins.